00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:30,150
[One Percent of Something]

9
00:00:40,180 --> 00:00:49,020
[Episode 6: Just Like Everyone Else: Spending Time Together in Our Busy Lives]

10
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,610
Did you contact the police?

11
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:58,600
Yes. They already start checking the security video, so the authenticity of the threat will be revealed soon.

12
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:01,240
As of now, they say it seems like a prank...

13
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:04,180
Like a prank? When I heard it's a bomb?

14
00:01:04,180 --> 00:01:06,830
Is this such a light matter?

15
00:01:06,830 --> 00:01:10,230
Check the manuals and secure the guest evacuation routes first.

16
00:01:10,230 --> 00:01:11,890
But if we do that, the hotel will be damaged—

17
00:01:11,890 --> 00:01:14,840
It'll be an even bigger problem if we don't do anything about it!

18
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:17,530
We should do everything we can first.

19
00:01:17,530 --> 00:01:20,790
And if it doesn't work, we'll activate the emergency system.

20
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:23,970
But Mr. Robinson is waiting for you right now.

21
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:25,690
Should I just cancel the meeting?

22
00:01:25,690 --> 00:01:27,460
We'll just do it.

23
00:01:27,460 --> 00:01:30,870
Instead, we'll keep it brief.

24
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:32,940
- We'll go to the dining hall right now.
- Yes, sir.

25
00:01:32,940 --> 00:01:36,940
If this isn't resolved within an hour, make sure you evacuate all the guests without fail.

26
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:38,660
Yes, CEO.

27
00:01:42,780 --> 00:01:44,990
Thank you so much. We appreciate your time.

28
00:01:44,990 --> 00:01:45,940
My pleasure.

29
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:48,200
And I'm very much looking forward to doing business with you in the future.

30
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,890
- Yes, see you later.
- Thank you so much.

31
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:54,660
- Hi, Mr. Robinson.
- Thank you, thank you very much for your time.

32
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:57,110
- Hope to see you again.
- Thank you.

33
00:01:57,110 --> 00:01:59,410
Let's move to the next scheduled activity.

34
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:14,260
- Mr. Robinson!
- What is this?

35
00:02:15,650 --> 00:02:16,890
Are you okay?

36
00:02:16,890 --> 00:02:18,220
- Call an ambulance.
- Yes, sir.

37
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:20,310
- Excuse me, call someone please.
- Yes, sir.

38
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:22,330
This is driving me crazy.

39
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:39,760
- Team Leader Gang, please go with them.
- Yes.

40
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:42,260
Yes, I understand. Don't worry.

41
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,330
But CEO, shouldn't you get out of here first?

42
00:02:45,330 --> 00:02:47,890
Have you seen a captain abandon his ship, even when it's sinking? Hurry and get in.

43
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,620
- Did you check this route?
- Yes, we did.

44
00:03:03,610 --> 00:03:05,970
Bubble Tea

45
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:21,150
Lee Jae In.

46
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:27,460
What is this? Even though it's been three years, it's ridiculous.

47
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:29,810
You're acting like you don't even know me although you saw me.

48
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:43,520
Is there something urgent?

49
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:47,170
Something looks serious.

50
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:50,220
- Why are you here?
- Because I wanted to see you.

51
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:53,690
I crossed the ocean for you, but you're being too indifferent.

52
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:57,820
Still, we were on the verge of getting married three years ago.

53
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:00,710
Luckily, we avoided that.

54
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:04,850
Well, the mean way you speak is still the same.

55
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:08,280
I'm sorry, but I am really busy. So please go your own way.

56
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,770
You still seem to be really busy.

57
00:04:11,650 --> 00:04:14,760
That's why you can't truly love.

58
00:04:15,610 --> 00:04:19,350
And that's why I said you were not meant for me.

59
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:22,110
You seemed to have forgotten since it happened three years ago.

60
00:04:22,110 --> 00:04:26,250
But the one who said we weren't meant to marry wasn't you, it was me.

61
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:29,170
What you turned down was the prenup I asked you to sign.

62
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:48,550
One second, go to the previous screen.

63
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,410
What is this? Where is this?

64
00:04:56,410 --> 00:04:58,810
It's a linen storage room that can be accessed only by employees.

65
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:27,670
It's a toy!

66
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:36,750
Did you submit all the evidence to the police?

67
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,910
Yes, they said they would analyze it immediately.

68
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:42,350
What kind of bast—

69
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:46,820
I mean, what kind of person would do something like this? Anyways, I think that's the end of all this.

70
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:49,280
Yes, no more threat calls either.

71
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:52,430
Double the number of guards patrolling the hotel.

72
00:05:52,430 --> 00:05:55,470
And tell the PR team to block the press completely from releasing anything related to this incident.

73
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:59,840
And we'll be reviewing the emergency manual again.

74
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:10,040
Ah, yes, my phone battery died. How is the situation?

75
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,180
They said it was a sudden heart attack

76
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:15,800
thankfully, he received emergency care in time, so he'll be okay.

77
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,000
Thank you for your hard work.

78
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,680
I'll send someone over soon. Until then, please monitor Mr. Robinson's condition.

79
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,630
Yes, I got it.

80
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:19,040
♫ Look here, my loving person ♫

81
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:25,780
♫ Now we are separating ♫

82
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:30,120
♫ I have a lot to say ♫

83
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:34,160
♫ I look at your pictures ♫

84
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:38,540
♫ and again tears fall ♫

85
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:45,050
♫ How much did I love you? ♫

86
00:07:45,050 --> 00:07:50,040
♫ Even if I stayed up 12 whole nights ♫

87
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:56,760
♫  I couldn’t say anything but with this short song ♫

88
00:07:56,760 --> 00:08:00,700
♫ it might be my last ♫

89
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:04,930
♫ I say my goodbye ♫

90
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:47,340
What are you doing here at this time?

91
00:08:47,340 --> 00:08:49,460
I am keeping my promise.

92
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,110
It is way past the time we promised to meet.

93
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:55,830
- What time do you think it is right now?
- I was really...

94
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:59,880
- I was really busy to the point where I couldn't move.
- You couldn't move what?

95
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,960
That was... the hotel suddenly had a bomb—

96
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:08,380
Anyway, it was an urgent situation.

97
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:12,140
- There's no time, let's at least go get tea.
- Everyone doesn't have enough time.

98
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:14,040
They just make the time.

99
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:17,030
- I told you I was really busy.
- What were you doing with your phone off?

100
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:20,410
Who turned off the phone? The battery—

101
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:24,720
Are you mad right now?

102
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,250
No.

103
00:09:28,330 --> 00:09:31,070
Not that I feel great,

104
00:09:32,450 --> 00:09:37,390
but we just need to fill up the numbers and dates.

105
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:39,500
So I am not going to get mad.

106
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:46,380
Just fill up the numbers and dates?

107
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:50,640
Is it not? What, then do you want me to go and get you coffee?

108
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:55,150
I told you, something came up. I was really busy.

109
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:57,210
No, at the hotel...

110
00:10:01,780 --> 00:10:03,780
[Team Leader Gang]

111
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:10,080
You really are busy.

112
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:15,100
It's Lee Jae In.

113
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:21,910
I understand. Were you able to get hold of the general manager?

114
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:25,880
I'll be back by ten.

115
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:35,410
It's really urgent. I will call you once I get there.

116
00:10:39,330 --> 00:10:42,080
Why do you even call me?

117
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:45,820
Let's talk next week. We have to end it quickly.

118
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,630
Well,

119
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,950
we're just dating anyway,

120
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:29,010
it's not like you're going to marry that guy.

121
00:11:33,490 --> 00:11:36,560
Why is he so busy all the time?

122
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,780
Yes.

123
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:58,330
I'll be there in 20 minutes.

124
00:11:58,330 --> 00:12:01,950
Did you contact Mr. Robinson's family, too?

125
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:07,060
If they want to come over, look into some flights to Korea.

126
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,720
Yes, yes.

127
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:14,720
This is driving me crazy.

128
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:25,620
You got stood up?

129
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:28,010
That's strange.

130
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:31,490
I thought that guy really liked you.

131
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,710
Does it make sense that he couldn't make it because he was too busy?

132
00:13:37,710 --> 00:13:39,590
Well, that part doesn't make sense.

133
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:44,370
Guys make time for the girls they like no matter what.

134
00:13:44,370 --> 00:13:46,380
- Right?
- Yep.

135
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:49,880
I didn't expect him to like me or anything.

136
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:53,640
He's always taking care of his work while we're dating.

137
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,880
So, are you disappointed?

138
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:59,860
Well, it's not... that it doesn't make me feel disappointed.

139
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:03,270
But I definitely realized one thing now.

140
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:05,380
What is it?

141
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:07,850
Not to misunderstand because we met a few times.

142
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:10,010
Don't fall for that guy.

143
00:14:10,010 --> 00:14:14,450
Just think of it as dating practice.

144
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:18,920
Excuse me, are you casting a spell?

145
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:22,170
Well, if nothing else works, I have to try that.

146
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:40,580
Let's go eat. I'll buy you something delicious, and a drink, too.

147
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:43,720
I'll give you two "Good Job" stamps for that.

148
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:46,670
Ah, thank you.

149
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:09,940
Yes.

150
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,370
I'm so hungry and tired.

151
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:15,770
I could die of exhaustion.

152
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:20,000
Me too. We've been working like dogs for three nights and days now.

153
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,980
Don't say stuff like that.

154
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:24,680
Here, it's an omega-3 pill.

155
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:28,800
Our CEO stayed up all three nights with work.

156
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:32,110
He must have the best stamina.

157
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:35,790
I guess he doesn't even need sleep since he has such a nasty temper.

158
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:42,220
Discuss with the PR team and deliver the Hawaii Hotel opening information to the media. Bring some opening gifts along.

159
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:44,750
I'll be back after reporting to the chairman.

160
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:48,690
And I'll also be gone for three hours. Please manage this place until I'm back.

161
00:15:48,690 --> 00:15:50,650
Yes, please get some rest today.

162
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:53,040
If anything comes up, we'll report to you immediately.

163
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,030
Thank you.

164
00:15:59,110 --> 00:16:02,360
Why is he bringing up the Hawaii Hotel? Wasn't that supposed to be confidential?

165
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:05,780
Well, to make sure that the media doesn't get a whiff of this,

166
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:08,540
we're giving them a decoy.

167
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,890
You still didn't know that?

168
00:16:10,890 --> 00:16:14,260
- Amateur.
- Amateur?

169
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:18,210
What's wrong with that?

170
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:20,130
I'm tired.

171
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,940
Should I get you some water?

172
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:31,260
It doesn't seem like a simple prank?

173
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:33,780
Reason?

174
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:37,620
The bomb was just a toy, but for us considering it was just a simple prank,

175
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:39,880
they put in too much prep work for this.

176
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:43,500
Do you have any ideas on the perpetrator? Any suspects?

177
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:50,600
Right now, there is only one person that seems suspicious to me.

178
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,370
Who is it?

179
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:56,420
Shouldn't you look into him if you have doubts and devise a plan for countermeasures?

180
00:16:57,080 --> 00:17:00,190
To be honest, the most suspicious person right now is you, Grandfather.

181
00:17:00,820 --> 00:17:04,360
My hotel isn't huge, but it just emerged from a deficit.

182
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:09,490
And since this business makes some cash, you're just waiting for a chance to steal it back, aren't you?

183
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:12,500
And you're doing tons of snooping on someone else's hotel.

184
00:17:13,230 --> 00:17:16,740
I'll give you another report when the results from the police investigation are out.

185
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:38,410
Why isn't she answering the phone?

186
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:45,080
Yes, Team Leader Gang.

187
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,180
That's a relief.

188
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:52,180
Still, you need to keep monitoring the media.

189
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:53,830
Yes, yes.

