♫ your light would disappear  ♫

215
00:20:51,580 --> 00:20:56,790
♫ That it would be this sad a night ♫

216
00:20:56,790 --> 00:21:01,790
♫ Tomorrow will be the first day I met you ♫

217
00:21:01,790 --> 00:21:06,260
♫ Today is the day I’m letting you go ♫

218
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:12,310
♫ Maybe the time that I was with you ♫

219
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:16,370
♫ Was just one night’s dream ♫

220
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:21,100
♫ I wanna go back to sleep ♫

221
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:24,690
♫ It half-felt like a dream ♫

222
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:29,160
♫ It half-felt like a lie ♫

223
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:34,260
♫ I thought those days weren’t possible ♫

224
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:39,340
Dammit!
♫ But when I fall asleep ♫

225
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:45,500
Open up!
♫ those days won’t ever come again ♫

226
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:54,860
♫ We close ourselves to each other ♫

227
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:13,400
Why are you here?

228
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:16,450
"Why are you here?" Aren't you getting home too late?

229
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:20,620
Mind your own business! Why are you here, when you're very busy?

230
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:22,370
I am busy right now.

231
00:22:22,370 --> 00:22:26,290
I barely made time for you but since you were late, Da Da...

232
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:28,660
I've wasted an hour and a half already!

233
00:22:28,660 --> 00:22:33,030
Is it my fault? Who told you to show up without calling first?

234
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:36,510
Why on earth didn't you answer the phone?

235
00:22:36,510 --> 00:22:40,530
Why do you always call me at a bad time?

236
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:45,370
Well, anyway, I needed to explain myself to you.

237
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:52,920
Go on, then. I should at least give you a chance to explain yourself.

238
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:57,460
Hurry up, already!

239
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,390
Right here?

240
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:03,640
Let's go and get something to eat first. I'm starving.

241
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:07,470
I had to skip dinner.

242
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:18,030
What kind of company doesn't even feed their employees and only makes them work?

243
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,210
I'm the CEO of that company, remember?

244
00:23:24,430 --> 00:23:26,540
A bomb threat? Oh, my!

245
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:31,080
You're not hurt anywhere, are you?

246
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:35,110
I didn't say a bomb really went off. It was just a prank.

247
00:23:35,110 --> 00:23:37,850
But I'm not sure it'll still be a prank in the end though.

248
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:40,590
Wow. That could have ended badly!

249
00:23:40,590 --> 00:23:44,310
If it had been a real bomb, it would have been really bad.

250
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:50,020
